<REFERENCE VARIABLE>

datatype varname   operator    value
int 		val		=		 10;
float 	val		=		 10.5F;
char 	val		=		 'a';

Datatype of reference variable is  "classname"

classname	varname	 operator   value
A 			 a1		  =		  new A();
B			 b1		  =		  new B();

Reference variable stores objects address.
->This variables are created inside method and should be used only within created method.

EXAMPLE:
public class A {
    public static void main(String args[]) {
     A a1= new A(); //a1 id local to main method 
      System.out.println(a1);
      a1.test();
    }
    public void test(){
     System.out.println(a1); //Error can not use a1 here because it is local,should not be used outside the method.
    }
}

EXAMPLE:
public class A {
    public static void main(String args[]) {
     A a1();// ERROR not initialise 
      System.out.println(a1);
    }
 
}

->Static reference has global access and these variables can be used anywhere in the program

EXAMPLE:
public class A {
    static A a1= new A();
    public static void main(String args[]) {
      System.out.println(a1);
     a1.test();
    }
    public void test(){
    System.out.println(a1);
    }
}


